value.value: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the stomach.
A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the gastrointestinal tract.
A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genitourinary system.
The presence of a diverticulum (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urethra.
Displacement of the big toe from its normal position.
Any abnormality of the spinal meninges, the system of membranes (dura mater, the arachnoid mater, and the pia mater) which envelops the spinal cord.
An outpouching of the spinal meninges.
Abnormality of the female genital system.

definition.value: Abnormality of the female internal or external genitalia.

value.value: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skeleton.
An abnormality of the Meninges, including any abnormality of the Dura mater, the Arachnoid mater, and the Pia mater.
Deposition of calcium salts in a tissue or location in which calcification does not normally occur.
A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the uterus.
The presence of a neoplasm of the urinary system.
A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genital system.

label.value: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract

value.value: An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.

definition.value: The upper urinary tract is a subdivision of urinary system which consists of the kidney and the ureters.

label.value: Abnormality of the lower urinary tract

value.value: An abnormality of the lower urinary tract.

definition.value: The lower urinary tract is a subdivision of urinary system which consists of the urinary bladder and the urethra.

value.value: A functional abnormality of the immune system.
An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries.
Abnormality of glucose homeostasis.

definition.value: An abnormality of any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of glucose within an organism or cell.

value.value: An abnormality of the concentration of glucose in the blood.
An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.
Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.
An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.
Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.
The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.
A morphological abnormality of a digit, i.e., of a finger or toe.

An abnormality of the coronary sinus, which is formed by the union of the great cardiac vein and the left marginal vein and terminates in the right atrium. The coronary sinus functions to o collect deoxygenated blood from the myocardium of the heart and drain it into the right atrium.
A venous pouch within the left ventricular wall, with a neck opening into the coronary sinus.
Neoplasm categorized according to type of histological abnormality.
Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm.
An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.
An abnormality of the appendicular skeletal system, consisting of the of the limbs, shoulder and pelvic girdles.
Abnormal calcification in the cardiovascular system.
Any structural anomaly of the kidney.
A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system.
A structural anomaly of the respiratory system.
An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.
A functional anomaly of the nervous system.
A structural anomaly of the nervous system.

Any anomaly of the inflammatory response, a response to injury or infection characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.
A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.
Abnormal structure of the gastrointestinal tract.
An abnormality of the anus or rectum.
A discrete abnormal tissue mass that protrudes into the lumen of the small intestine and is attached to the intestinal wall either by a stalk, pedunculus, or a broad base.
An anomaly of the neck of the uterus (lower part of the uterus), called the uterine cervix.

definition.value: Any anomaly of the digestive system, a collection of organs that is made up of the gastrointestinal tract and the liver, pancreas, and gallbladder. The gastrointestinal tract is a series of hollow organs joined in a long, twisting tube from the mouth to the anus, including the mouth, esophagus, stomach, small intestine, large intestine and anus.
A structural anomaly of the digestive system.
Any structural anomaly of the bladder.

value.value: A growth protruding from the mucous membrane of the ureter. Ureteral polyps can be attached to the ureter by a broad base or a thin stalk.
